comments.comment_body:
This one is too easy, many of us have been playing the what if game from day one on a litany of Trump actions.

It's a simple inverse equation; 

Fox News and republicans love the Trump action = would demonize it if Obama had done it.

Senator Lindsey Graham;
“I really do believe that the best person — group of people — to pick a president are the voters, not a bunch of partisan politicians.”

Ever Hear of the Electoral college ?

@Bret Stephens
"Yet for the overwhelming majority of Americans, life is pretty much the same under Trump as it was under Obama."

Stop right there, Bret. Life is NOT pretty much the same under Trump as it was under Obama:
 - if you're a member of the LBGQT community and have interest in serving in the military;
 - if you receive Social Security Disability benefits and are about to be subjected to a strict review; 
- if you receive SNAP benefits;
- if you receive your healthcare benefits under Obamacare and may lose that coverage due to ongoing Republican-funded lawsuits, rules changes and funding cuts.
- if you are a woman living in a red state and would like to avail yourself of affordable reproductive health care.
- if you are a member of any class of people who will be hurt by ongoing rule changes, funding cuts.

Just having to live with one or more of these foreboding changes would be enough to cause any vulnerable person deep emotional pain and worry. 
The Trump reign is a cautionary tale. You don't realize how precious your rights are until one or more are taken away from you.
